John Gibbs, from Michigan, has been nominated to be the Director of the Office of Personnel Management for a four-year term. Currently serving as the Acting Assistant Secretary for Community Planning and Development at the United States Department of Housing and Urban Development, Gibbs oversees an annual budget of $8 billion for programs addressing homelessness, community development, and disaster relief. He has led successful deployment of over $9 billion in CARES Act funds in response to the coronavirus pandemic. Prior to his government service, Gibbs led non-profit teams in Japan, training them on using technology to reach vulnerable populations and implementing homeless outreach strategies for Japanese churches. He also worked as a software engineer in Silicon Valley for companies like Symantec, Palm, and Apple, contributing to the development of notable technology products such as intrusion detection software and the first version of the iPhone. Gibbs is a published author, with academic writings on the application of Behavioral Economics to policymaking. He holds a B.S. in Computer Science from Stanford University and a Master in Public Administration from Harvard University's Kennedy School of Government.